HEADWORD: Nastiness
<hw>Nas"ti*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
nasty; extreme filthiness; dirtiness; also, indecency;
obscenity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>nastiness</qex> of Plautus and Aristophanes.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nasturtion</ent>⟦br⟧
